section.section:
Any plan established by the Board of County Commissioners under this section shall include provisions regarding:
Retirement age eligibility;
Retirement based on years of active service, regardless of age;
Early retirement eligibility;
Disability retirement;
Death benefits for a spouse or children;
Cost-of-living adjustments; and
Cash refund of contributions for participants terminating their employment.

text.section:
In accordance with § 21-1119 of the Transportation Article, the County Commissioners of Garrett County may:
Designate a county road within the county to be an "emergency snow route";
Regulate travel upon such emergency snow route;
Provide for method of declaring a snow emergency;
Prohibit the parking or abandoning of a vehicle on an emergency snow route during a snow emergency; and
Authorize the removal of a vehicle parked or abandoned on an emergency snow route during a snow emergency.

section.section:
In this subsection, "government organization" includes:
A county;
A board of education;
A municipal corporation; or
A government cooperative purchasing organization.
